    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "b5358ca9"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Make a prediction on a new review\n",
        "\n",
        "To see how your model performs on a new piece of text (what you might be referring to as a 'new random feature'), we need to follow these steps:\n",
        "\n",
        "1.  **Define a new review:** Provide the text you want the model to classify.\n",
        "2.  **Preprocess the new review:** Apply all the same cleaning and stemming steps that were applied to your training data (removing HTML, converting to lowercase, removing special characters, removing stopwords, stemming).\n",
        "3.  **Vectorize the preprocessed review:** Use the `CountVectorizer` (`cv`) fitted on your training data to transform the new review into the numerical format the model expects.\n",
        "4.  **Load the trained model:** Load one of your saved models (e.g., `MultinomialNB` which had the best accuracy).\n",
        "5.  **Predict sentiment:** Use the loaded model to predict the sentiment (positive or negative) of the new review."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 73,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6f56c88a",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "2b606048-1efc-4681-99c9-654f7d7b517f"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Original Review: This movie was absolutely fantastic! I loved every minute of it and would highly recommend it to everyone.\n",
            "Processed Review: movi absolut fantast love everi minut would highli recommend everyon\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Example of a new review\n",
        "new_review_text = \"This movie was absolutely fantastic! I loved every minute of it and would highly recommend it to everyone.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define a function to preprocess a single review, replicating previous steps\n",
        "def preprocess_single_review(text):\n",
        "    # 1. Clean HTML tags (using the existing clean_html function)\n",
        "    text = clean_html(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 2. Convert to lowercase (using the existing convert_lower function)\n",
        "    text = convert_lower(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 3. Remove special characters (using the existing remove_special function)\n",
        "    text = remove_special(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 4. Remove stopwords (using a corrected, self-contained version of remove_stopwords)\n",
        "    # The original remove_stopwords used a global list 'x' that was cleared, which is fine\n",
        "    # when applied to a DataFrame column, but for a single string, we'll ensure it's self-contained.\n",
        "    words = []\n",
        "    for i in text.split():\n",
        "        if i not in stopwords.words('english'):\n",
        "            words.append(i)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 5. Stem words (using a corrected, self-contained version for single review)\n",
        "    stemmed_words = []\n",
        "    for word in words:\n",
        "        stemmed_words.append(ps.stem(word))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 6. Join back into a string\n",
        "    return \" \".join(stemmed_words)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Preprocess the new review\n",
        "processed_new_review = preprocess_single_review(new_review_text)\n",
        "print(f\"Original Review: {new_review_text}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Processed Review: {processed_new_review}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 74,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d3962876",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "ac5183e4-18ae-4dfc-b04b-b019a944b2eb"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Vectorized review shape: (1, 20000)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "new_review_vectorized = tfidf.transform([processed_new_review])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Vectorized review shape: {new_review_vectorized.shape}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 76,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "68029330",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "fe2eded1-4056-4d8a-ac37-7aad2ef3c4a4"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Predicted Sentiment for the new review: Positive\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import pickle\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load the single model from the saved pickle file\n",
        "# Based on the notebook, a LinearSVC model was saved to 'model.pkl'.\n",
        "with open('model.pkl', 'rb') as file:\n",
        "    loaded_model = pickle.load(file)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use the loaded model for prediction\n",
        "prediction = loaded_model.predict(new_review_vectorized)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Interpret the prediction\n",
        "sentiment_map = {1: 'Positive', 0: 'Negative'}\n",
        "predicted_sentiment = sentiment_map[prediction[0]]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Predicted Sentiment for the new review: {predicted_sentiment}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "89cad13f"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Test with a negative review"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "42cdea22",
        "outputId": "f15f610b-5fb1-45d3-eca4-aa272235cb55"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Example of a new negative review\n",
        "new_review_text_negative = \"This movie was utterly terrible. I regretted every second of watching it.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Preprocess the new review using the existing function\n",
        "processed_new_review_negative = preprocess_single_review(new_review_text_negative)\n",
        "print(f\"Original Review: {new_review_text_negative}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Processed Review: {processed_new_review_negative}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Vectorize the preprocessed review using the fitted TF-IDF vectorizer\n",
        "new_review_vectorized_negative = tfidf.transform([processed_new_review_negative])\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Vectorized negative review shape: {new_review_vectorized_negative.shape}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use the loaded model to predict the sentiment\n",
        "prediction_negative = loaded_model.predict(new_review_vectorized_negative)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Interpret the prediction\n",
        "predicted_sentiment_negative = sentiment_map[prediction_negative[0]]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Predicted Sentiment for the new negative review: {predicted_sentiment_negative}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 77,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Original Review: This movie was utterly terrible. I regretted every second of watching it.\n",
            "Processed Review: movi utterli terribl regret everi second watch\n",
            "Vectorized negative review shape: (1, 20000)\n",
            "Predicted Sentiment for the new negative review: Negative\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
